<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Basidiomata distinctly small. A pileus a bit slimy when moist. Stipe light yellow, base turning to light brown with age. Cheilocystidia common in clavate with rounded apex, rarely fusiform. Pileipellis occasionally with coarse excrescences.</paragraph>
